==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penthouse
<hw>Pent"house`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A corruption of
<ets>pentice</ets>.]</ety> <def>A shed or roof sloping from the main
wall or building, as over a door or window; a lean-to. Also
figuratively.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>penthouse</xex> of his eyes.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 2. An apartment at the top of a building. It is often the most
luxuriously appointed apartment, and is thus used as a metaphor for
luxurious living. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penthouse</ent>⟦br⟧

